{"title": "Southpaw Advantage", "content": "Since the vast majority of the human population is right hand dominant, meeting someone who is the opposite isn't something most people would expect. Some would think that it would be a handicap because left-handed people live in a world that is geared toward those who are right-handed; however, it has quite a few perks. Left-handed characters often have to adapt to the world by forcing themselves to use their right hand, which can, over time, cause them to be adept at using both of their hands/feet (as well as both sides of their body).\n\nBeing left-handed can give a character an edge in various areas of expertise such as sports and combat because most of their opponents aren't used to competing against lefties since they are the minority of the population.\n\nTraditionally, baseball fields were oriented so that the batter, catcher, and umpire faced east to ensure that the setting sun wasn't in their eyes. As a result, when a pitcher is on the mound facing home plate, his left hand pointed south, so lefty pitchers came to be known as southpaws. The term has since entered general usage to indicate left-handed people which is how the trope got its name.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SouthPawAdvantage", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AokiDensetsuShoot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/BlackCat", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DiamondNoAce", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Haikyuu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/HajimeNoIppo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/KaguyaSamaLoveIsWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/LyricalNanoha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Shirobako", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/VividStrike", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BackToTheFuture", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Rocky", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Rocky", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RockyII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Tron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAndFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TortallUniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Dery